g.text: DOCUMENT EVERYTHINGand sort out what’s important afterwards! This project is sited within a 3’ flood plane putting all nearby properties and people at an unfair risk in East Boston, a neighborhood already burdened with a disproportionate amount of regional and industrial infrastructure.COMMUNICATE ACCURATELYThe history of 338 East Eagle Street and of East Boston to visitors so they can empathize with the deep history of unjust infrastructure alongside Eversource’s malpractices. Only then can we proceed with making a fair future for the neighborhood. Concessions must be made for violations in the past. UNDERSTAND DEEPLYEast Boston as a diverse neighborhood inhabited by passionate people who care about their homes. Before a new project is approved, there needs to be a clearly communicated, with translators if necessary, actively involved process that accounts for all of the different kinds of people that will be effected by that project’s construction. ORGANIZE EFFECTIVELY physically and digitally. Spread awareness of the situation’ss essential conditions. Create spaces where people can recollect, gather, and vocalize their needs. Don’t be afraid to work outside of the systems that have failed you.
